messages.content: I'm really stressed about work lately
Tell me more at work?
My boss keeps piling on more projects and I can't keep up
That seems overwhelming. How long has this been happening?
About 3 months now. Ever since Sarah left the team
Ah, so you're basically doing two people's jobs now?
Exactly! And when I try to bring it up, my boss just says 'we're all stretched thin'
Ugh, that's so frustrating. You're drowning and they're just dismissing it. Have you been able to talk to anyone else about this?
Not really. I don't want to seem like I'm complaining
You're not complaining though - you're dealing with an impossible workload. That's a real problem, not whining.

messages.content: I've been really anxious lately
What's that been like for you?
I can't stop thinking about all the things that could go wrong
Are these specific things or just general worry?
Specific. Like what if I mess up this presentation at work, or what if my car breaks down
How often are these thoughts popping up?
Constantly. I'll be watching TV and suddenly I'm thinking about the presentation
That feels like it would be exhausting. Your brain won't give you a break.
Exactly! And then I get anxious about being anxious. It's like a loop
Oh man, the anxiety about anxiety is the worst. It's like your brain is trolling you.
Yes! And people keep saying 'just don't worry about it' like it's that simple
Right? If you could just stop worrying, you would have done that already. That advice is so unhelpful.

metadata.empathy_development: General anxiety → specific examples → frequency/intensity → emotional toll → shared frustration with unhelpful advice

messages.content: I have no energy for anything anymore
When did this start have you been feeling this way?
A few weeks now. I used to love going out with friends but now it feels like too much work
Even things you normally enjoy feel overwhelming?
Yeah, my friend invited me to dinner last week and I made an excuse not to go
What was going through your mind when she asked?
Just thinking about getting dressed and driving there and making conversation... it felt impossible
Like each step was this huge mountain to climb?
Exactly. And then I felt guilty for canceling, which made me feel worse
So now you're dealing with the original exhaustion plus guilt on top of it.
And my friend probably thinks I don't want to see her
That's rough. You're stuck between not having the energy and worrying about hurting people you care about.

messages.content: My family is driving me crazy
What's happening with them?
My mom keeps asking when I'm going to get married and have kids
How often does this come up?
Every time I talk to her. Last week she sent me a link to a dating app
Oh wow, she's really not being subtle about it.
No, and the thing is, I do want those things eventually. But I'm only 26
So it's not that she's wrong about what you want, it's the pressure and timing?
Right. And she acts like I'm running out of time or something
That must make you feel like nothing you're doing right now matters to her.
Yeah, like my career and my life now don't count because I'm not married
That's incredibly invalidating. You're building a whole life and she's focused on this one piece that's missing.

metadata.empathy_development: General family frustration → specific behavior → frequency/intensity → deeper issue of timing → feeling invalidated → understanding the real hurt

Yeah, like my career and my life now don't count because I'm not married
That's incredibly invalidating. You're building a whole life and she's focused on this one piece that's missing.

The guessing game is torture. You just want to know where you stand.
